<collectingCountry box="[368,441,764,788]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: North Region (AM) (
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser" box="[689,846,764,788]" firstAuthor="Nieser" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="139 - 151" refId="ref40708" refString="Nieser, N. (1970 d) Hydrometridae of the Suriname and the Amazon, with additional records of other neotropical species (Hemiptera - Heteroptera). Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas, 12, 139 - 151." type="journal article" year="1970" yearSuffix="d">Nieser 1970d</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,598,871,896]" box="[151,598,871,896]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1796" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1796" box="[151,469,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrometridae" genus="Hydrometra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,469,871,896]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,291,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Hydrometra</emphasis>
Latreille, 1796
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(7 species)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,943,1111]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Comments: 
<emphasis box="[293,555,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1796" box="[293,429,944,968]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrometridae" genus="Hydrometra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hydrometra</taxonomicName>
fuanicana
</emphasis>
Drake, 1954 was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[972,1026,944,967]" name="Peru" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Peru</collectingCountry>
, but in the checklist of American 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[151,321,980,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hydrometridae</taxonomicName>
provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Drake and Lauck" box="[469,745,980,1004]" firstAuthor="Drake" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="43 - 52" refId="ref37217" refString="Drake, C. J. &amp; Lauck, D. R. (1959) Descriptions, synonymy, and check-list of American Hydrometridae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera). Great Basin Naturalist, 29, 43 - 52." type="journal article" year="1959">Drake and Lauck (1959)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[757,825,980,1004]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Brazil</collectingCountry>
is the only country cited for this species. This is probably the result of a mistake, not a correction or new record. On the same list, a similar error occurs in the distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Jaczewski, 1928" authorityName="Jaczewski" authorityYear="1928" box="[232,579,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrometridae" genus="Hydrometra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sztolcmani">
<emphasis box="[232,386,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. sztolcmani</emphasis>
Jaczewski, 1928
</taxonomicName>
, which is wrongly recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[959,1080,1052,1076]" name="Guatemala" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
instead of 
<collectingCountry box="[1204,1275,1052,1076]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, as pointed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bachmann" box="[151,356,1087,1111]" firstAuthor="Bachmann" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="143 - 146" refId="ref34110" refString="Bachmann, A. O. (1977) Nota sobre las Hydrometridae de la Argentina (Heteroptera). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 35, 143 - 146." type="journal article" year="1977">Bachmann (1977)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
